<dl id="n12214m"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12214m">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12214m"> 214(m)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> took off his body <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n12214m"><li>FW 98.16 </li><li><a href="../../flex/d/lexd.htm#n12214m">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/d/l39d.htm#n12214m">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n12214m">MS BL 47472-161</ms> </li><li>JJA 46:061 <a name="d23d" href="../../ff/fdra/dda.htm#d23d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/d/d23d.htm#n12214m">Draft: I.4&sect;2.3</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Cette repr&eacute;sentation d&apos;une immortalit&eacute; qui se d&eacute;roule en r&eacute;incarnations est apparemment en contradiction avec celle d&apos;une survie et d&apos;une mort incompl&egrave;te que nous venons d&apos;examiner, car la transmigration ne peut commencer qu&apos;au moment o&ugrave; la mort a produit toutes ses cons&eacute;quences et quand le corps est compl&egrave;tement d&eacute;saffect&eacute;. <br><font color="green">[This representation of an immortality which unfolds in reincarnations apparently contradicts that of a survival or of an incomplete death which we have just examined, because the transmigration can only start at the moment when death has produced all of its effects and <mark>when the corpse is completely gone</mark>]</font> <small> Stefan Czarnowski, <a name="SCSP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SCSP"><cite title="source">Le culte des h&eacute;ros et ses conditions sociale: saint Patrick, h&eacute;ros nationale de l'Irlande</cite></a> (1919) LXXXI</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
